export const sourceCode = "---\ntitle: Effects\n---\n\n# Effects\n\nEvery timeline entry is one **effect**, discriminated by `action`. They fall into\nfive lanes: camera, navigation, cursor, interaction and timing.\n\n<Frame id=\"fx-grid\" intent=\"effect-grid\">\n  <div className=\"tk-fx-grid\">\n    <Frame id=\"fx-zoom\"><div className=\"tk-fx\">zoom-in / out</div></Frame>\n    <Frame id=\"fx-highlight\"><div className=\"tk-fx\">highlight</div></Frame>\n    <Frame id=\"fx-cursor\"><div className=\"tk-fx\">cursor-move</div></Frame>\n  </div>\n</Frame>\n\nInteractions actually touch the app. `type-down` writes into a real field:\n\n<Frame id=\"fx-type\" intent=\"email-field\">\n  <input className=\"tk-fx-input\" placeholder=\"type-down writes here…\" aria-label=\"effects demo input\" />\n</Frame>\n\n<DemoGif section=\"effects\" caption=\"zoom → highlight → cursor → shake → type — the whole vocabulary in one pass.\" />\n\n<Divider />\n\n## Reference\n\nShared optional fields on every effect: `frameId`, `delayBefore`, `delayAfter`,\n`note`. `easing` is one of `linear · ease-in · ease-out · ease-in-out · spring`.\n\n| Action | Key fields | Default duration |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `click` | `frameId`, `showRipple`, `soundProfile` | ~500ms |\n| `type-down` | `frameId`, `text`, `typingSpeed`, `mistakes` | `text.length × speed` |\n| `drag-and-drop` | `frameId`, `destFrameId`/`destX,destY` | 800ms |\n| `shake` | `frameId`, `intensity` | 500ms |\n| `zoom-in` | `frameId?`, `scale`, `transformOrigin` | 1200ms |\n| `zoom-out` | — | 900ms |\n| `scroll-up` / `scroll-down` | `distance` | 700ms |\n| `cursor-move` | `destFrameId`/`destX,destY`, `curve` | 700ms |\n| `highlight` | `frameId`, `dimOpacity`, `padding` | 1500ms |\n| `wait` | `duration` | 1000ms |\n\nAll are strongly typed with Zod; the [timesheet](/timesheet) schema rejects an\nunplayable sheet before a single frame is recorded.";
